               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18510818-1764-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-1764-18510818 t18510818-1764-offence-1 t18510818-1764-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>1764. <persName id="def1-1764-18510818" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1764-18510818" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1764-18510818" type="age" value="28"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1764-18510818" type="surname" value="RICHARDSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1764-18510818" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES RICHARDSON</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18510818-1764-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18510818-1764-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18510818-1764-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="burglary"></interp>, burglariously breaking and entering the dwelling-house of <persName id="t18510818-name-1022" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1022" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1022" type="surname" value="YOUNG"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1022" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18510818-1764-offence-1 t18510818-name-1022"></join>John Young</persName>; with intent to steal.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CAARTEEN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution</hi>,</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510818-name-1023" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1023" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1023" type="surname" value="CHAPPLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1023" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>FREDERICK CHAPPLE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am waiter at the White Hart public-house, Park-street, Southwark, which is kept by Mr. Young, it is in St. Saviour's parish. On Wednesday evening, 13th Aug., between 8 and 9 o'clock, the prisoner came and went into the bagatelle-room, which is up-stairs, and adjoins my master's bed-room—a panel of the bed-room door has been broken, and is mended with a piece of sacking, nailed over it inside, and then there is a piece of wood nailed across the sacking to keep it firm—about half-past 9, I missed the prisoner from the bagatelle-room, where I had seen him ten minutes before—I went down-stairs, spoke to Mrs. Young, and in conse<lb></lb>quence of what she said I went up-stairs again, and while going up saw the prisoner coming through the panel of the door—he came down-stairs, passed me on the stairs, and I followed him to the door—Mrs. Young had followed me op-stairs, and went into the bed-room—at the front-door the prisoner looked round', saw me, and ran away—I followed, and caught him about twenty yards from the house—he <hi rend="italic">up</hi> with his fist and ran. down Fishmonger-alley—I cried, "Stop thief!" and he was stopped in the alley by Richards—when he was stopped I saw him stoop down by the side of the wall, and heard something jingle—a light was afterwards brought, and the policeman picked up two skeleton keys on the spot in my presence.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. O'BRIEN</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How many persons were in the bagatelle-room? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About six—the bed-room door is at the side of the bagatelle-room door—half the panel was out—a man must kneel down to get through—I do not know in what condition the door was that evening—I know it was half-past 9 o'clock when I missed him, because there is a clock in the bar and I went down to inquire whether he had passed the bar.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510818-name-1024" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1024" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1024" type="surname" value="YOUNG"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1024" type="given" value="ELIZA"></interp>ELIZA YOUNG</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of John Young, who keeps the White Hart. On 23rd Aug. Chappie came to me about twenty minutes or half-past 9 o'clock; I followed him up-stairs, and as we were going up I saw the prisoner, but did not see where he came from—I said, "Watch him! watch him!"—he was then on the same stair as me—he darted off out of the house as quick as possible, and Chappie followed him—I went up-stairs and found the aperture in my door had been opened, the wood was entirely removed, and the sacking from one side, and left on the nails on the other—the door was still locked—I had</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185108180182"></xptr>
               <p>seen it about 9, or a few minutes before, and it was quite safe then—I searched the room, but missed nothing.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510818-name-1025" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1025" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1025" type="surname" value="MORRIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1025" type="given" value="JOHN ROBERT"></interp>JOHN ROBERT MORRIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a ginger-beer manufacturer, at 13, Fish<lb></lb>monger-alley. On 13th Aug., about a quarter to 10 o'clock, I was at my door talking to a neighbour, and heard a cry of "Stop thief!"—I got into a corner by Mr. Watson's premises—the prisoner ran up to me, I said, "Halloo!" and he <hi rend="italic">chucked</hi> something over the wall into Mr. Watson's yard—I afterwards went and spoke to Mr. Watson.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510818-name-1026" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1026" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1026" type="surname" value="WATSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1026" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WATSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a hat-manufacturer, at 76, Redcross-street. Mr. Morris spoke to me—I went into my yard, which adjoins Fishmonger, alley, and there found this case of picklocks (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>).</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510818-name-1027" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1027" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1027" type="surname" value="RICHARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510818-name-1027" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS RICHARDS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, M</hi> 10). I was in Fishmonger-alley on 13th Aug., about 10 minutes to 10 o'clock, heard a cry of "Stop thief!" and saw the prisoner running towards me—I laid hold of him, and he said, "Let me go, you b——r"—he took his hand from his pocket, and stooped down, and I heard something <hi rend="italic">jink</hi>—I called for a light, and at his feet found there two skeleton-keys (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>)—Chappie came up, and I took the prisoner to the station—I afterwards went to the prosecutor's, and found these keys would unlock all the drawers.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18510818-1764-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
